<subSubSection pageId="106" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[325,608,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[325,608,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Phylladiorhynchus pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the group of species having 2 median epigastric spines, the hepatic margin unarmed and 2 spines on the anterior branchial margin. This species is easily characterized by the absence of subapical spines. The new species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[872,991,547,573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbeae">
<emphasis box="[872,991,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. barbeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1067,1286,547,573]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1297,1389,547,573]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,328,583,609]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. However, both species can be distinguished on the basis of the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
- The anterior margin of thoracic sternite 3 is straight or slightly convex, and produced anterolaterally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbeae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. barbeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas this margin is medially produced, and anterolaterally rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[1081,1170,655,680]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[1081,1170,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
- Antennal article 3 is often armed with a distomesial spine in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[927,1047,691,717]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbeae">
<emphasis box="[927,1047,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. barbeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas this article is unarmed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,240,727,752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[151,240,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
- The P2–4 propodi are slender in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[612,731,763,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbeae">
<emphasis box="[612,731,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. barbeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–7 × as long as wide), whereas they are stout (&lt;5.8 × as long as wide) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[281,370,799,824]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[281,370,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
- The colour pattern of the carapace and pleon are whitish, with reddish patches, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[1169,1289,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbeae">
<emphasis box="[1169,1289,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. barbeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the colour pattern is green or light orange, with no reddish patches, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[896,985,871,896]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[896,985,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,150,1005]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
The genetic divergences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[578,666,907,932]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[578,666,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[720,840,907,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbeae">
<emphasis box="[720,840,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. barbeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were 7% (COI) and 3% (16S). The two sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,240,943,968]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[151,240,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[308,443,943,969]" name="Madagascar" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
were divergent by 0.6% for 16S. The specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodríguez-Flores &amp; Macpherson &amp; Machordom" authorityYear="2021" box="[1026,1115,943,968]" class="Malacostraca" family="Galatheidae" genus="Phylladiorhynchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepei">
<emphasis box="[1026,1115,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">P. pepei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
range in size range from 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" unit="mm" value="2.85" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.5">2.5 to 3.2 mm</quantity>
postorbital carapace length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
